cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.IR 

The paper proposes a novel technique for buried object detection using convolutional neural networks (CNN) and ground penetrating radar (GPR) data. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the use of autoencoders for anomaly detection and the analysis of volumetric data suggest that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-categories. The paper also involves the use of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques for landmine detection. Finally, the paper may also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category, as it involves the analysis of data acquired through GPR.
